{"title_page": "Tarzan of Manisa (film)", "text_new": "{{short description|1994 film}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Tarzan of Manisa\n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| director       = [[Orhan O\u011fuz]]\n| producer       = \n| writer         = [[Nuray Oguz]]\n| starring       = [[Talat Bulut]]\n| music          = \n| cinematography = \n| editing        = \n| distributor    = \n| released       = {{Film date|df=yes|1994}}\n| runtime        = 101 minutes\n| country        = Turkey\n| language       = Turkish\n| budget         = \n}}\n\n'''''Tarzan of Manisa''''' ({{lang-tr|'''Manisa Tarzan\u0131'''}}) is a 1994 Turkish [[drama film]] directed by [[Orhan O\u011fuz]].<ref name=\"NY Times\">{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/movies/movie/134670/Manisa-Tarzani/overview |title=Tarzan of Manisa |accessdate=1 October 2015 |work=NY Times}}</ref> The film was selected as the Turkish entry for the [[Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film|Best Foreign Language Film]] at the [[67th Academy Awards]], but was not accepted as a nominee.<ref>Margaret Herrick Library, Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Talat Bulut]] as Ahmet Bedevi '[[Tarzan of Manisa]]'\n* [[Serap Saglar]]\n* [[Pinar Afsar]]\n* [[Ayton Sert]]\n* [[Kutay K\u00f6kt\u00fcrk]]\n* [[\u00d6zlem Savas]]\n* [[Nihat Nikerel]]\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of submissions to the 67th Academy Awards for Best Foreign Language Film]]\n* [[List of Turkish submissions for the Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|0111366|Tarzan of Manisa}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Tarzan Of Manisa}}\n[[Category:1994 films]]\n[[Category:1994 drama films]]\n[[Category:Turkish films]]\n[[Category:Turkish drama films]]\n[[Category:Turkish-language films]]\n{{Turkey-film-stub}}\n{{1990s-drama-film-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|1994 film}}\n{{use dmy dates|date=March 2017}}\n{{Info